I haven't made this yet but I have the actual magazine from 1999 and the recipe states 1/3 cup of hazelnuts--I wonder if that's why one reviewer said the hazelnuts overpowered? Will try it w 1/3 and see what the topping feels like before adding additional.

Rating: 4
I LOVE this recipe. Although I have not made it with hazelnuts, but almonds and pecans. I have gotten rave reviews from EVERYONE who has tried it!!!

Rating: 1
This recipe, as written, is not very good. The hazelnuts are overpowering and if you used ripe pears, the sugar in the fruit filling is too much and is way too sweet. The overall effect is syrupy fruit with a fairly dry crust. You can omit the hazelnuts, substitute with almonds, decrease the sugar in the filling, add cinnamon, all spice and nutmeg to the recipe to improve it but it wouldn't be the recipe they have provided here.

